  "prompt": "Is there an online calculator that shows work?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several online calculators that show the steps or work involved in solving problems. These tools are particularly useful for learning and understanding how to approach various mathematical, algebraic, and calculus problems. Here are a few popular ones:\n\n### 1. **Symbolab**  \n   - **Website**: [https://www.symbolab.com](https://www.symbolab.com)  \n   - **Features**: Solves algebra, calculus, and other math problems while showing step-by-step solutions.  \n   - **Pros**: Covers a wide range of topics, from basic arithmetic to advanced calculus.  \n\n### 2. **Mathway**  \n   - **Website**: [https://www.mathway.com](https://www.mathway.com)  \n   - **Features**: Provides step-by-step solutions for algebra, calculus, trigonometry, and more.  \n   - **Pros**: Easy to use and includes a mobile app.  \n\n### 3. **Wolfram Alpha**  \n   - **Website**: [https://www.wolframalpha.com](https://www.wolframalpha.com)  \n   - **Features**: Offers detailed solutions and explanations for math, science, and engineering problems.  \n   - **Pros**: Highly advanced and comprehensive; covers a vast range of topics.  \n\n### 4. **Desmos**  \n   - **Website**: [https://www.desmos.com](https://www.desmos.com)  \n   - **Features**: Focuses on graphing and visual explanations for equations and functions.  \n   - **Pros**: Interactive and great for visualizing math concepts.  \n\n### 5. **Cymath**  \n   - **Website**: [https://www.cymath.com](https://www.cymath.com)  \n   - **Features**: Solves algebra and calculus problems with detailed steps.  \n   - **Pros**: Simple interface and free to use.  \n\n### 6. **QuickMath**  \n   - **Website**: [https://quickmath.com](https://quickmath.com)  \n   - **Features**: Solves equations, inequalities, and other math problems step-by-step.  \n   - **Pros**: Straightforward and easy to navigate.  \n\nEach of these tools has its strengths, so you can choose the one that best fits your needs!",
